OpenVPN
 additional ciphers on Debian/Ubuntu

Support AES-GCM, AES-CTR and AES-XTS cipher modes.
Support EVP_AEAD ciphers when installed EVP_AEAD APIs supported OpenSSL
 (https://github.com/h-yamamo/openssl-chacha20poly1305).

Reference:
  https://community.openvpn.net/openvpn/attachment/ticket/301
  [0001-Add-AEAD-cipher-modes.patch]

Build package:

*Debian 8 (jessie)
  (in some directory)
  apt-get -d source openvpn
  tar xf openvpn_2.3.4.orig.tar.gz
  cd openvpn-2.3.4
  tar xvf ../openvpn_2.3.4-5.debian.tar.xz
  cp -a (this repository)/jessie/debian/* debian/
  debuild -uc -us

*Ubuntu 14.04.2 LTS (Trusty Tahr)
  (in some directory)
  apt-get -d source openvpn
  tar xf openvpn_2.3.2.orig.tar.gz
  cd openvpn-2.3.2
  tar xvf ../openvpn_2.3.2-7ubuntu3.1.debian.tar.gz
  cp -a (this repository)/trusty/debian/* debian/
  debuild -uc -us

Usage with ChaCha20-Poly1305 cipher:
  openvpn --cipher aead.chacha20-poly1305 ...

Show available ciphers:
  openvpn --show-ciphers

